<div id="content">
  <h1 id="pageName">National Research and Training Center (NRTC) </h1>
  <h2 id="pageName">/Training and Education </h2>
  <div class="story">
    <h3>Hope for Healing:  Self-Help for Women Trauma Survivors</h3>
    <p>Hope for Healing
      is a self-help support group facilitator's manual for women mental health
      consumers who are survivors of physical or sexual abuse and are in the
      initial stages of abuse recovery. Topics addressed include creating safety
      and coping with crises, managing intense emotions, flashbacks, and self-injury;
      facing fears; therapeutic limit-setting; and spirituality as part of recovery.
      Information about different types of abuse and their effects on current
      functioning is provided. The curriculum was designed to be led by experienced
      peers and/or nonconsumers. Special attention is paid to self-care techniques
      for the group facilitators, particularly if they are in recovery themselves.      </p>
    <p>You may <a href="../download/hope_for_healing.manual.pdf"><strong>download a free copy of the manual now</strong></a>, or order a copy of this manual from the <em>Women's
        Resources</em> page of
        the <a href="../download/publist.pdf">Publications
        list [PDF, 223K] </a>. Orders cannot be taken over the Internet. You
        will need to print off an order form that can either be faxed or mailed
        to the Center. </p>
  </div>
  <div class="story"></div>
